# CampIn Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Project Overview
CampIn is India's community-first camping platform — "Airbnb for Camping in India."
Built with React 19 + Vite 7 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS 4.
Read CLAUDE.md for full project context before starting any task.
Read docs/ folder for all strategic documentation.

## Mandatory Design Rules
- Colors: Forest Green #1F3D2B (primary), Orange #E67E22 (accent ONLY), Off White #F7F5F2 (page bg)
- Font: Inter only. Never use any other font family.
- Body text: #5F5F5F (never pure black #000)
- Border radius: 16px cards, 12px buttons
- No dark mode. No gradients. No 3D effects.
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Tailwind utility classes only

## Code Style
- Functional components with TypeScript
- Export default for all components
- Import order: React hooks → Router → External → Internal data → Internal components
- Use design token classes: text-forest, bg-offwhite, text-orange, text-textgrey
- Mobile-first: base = mobile, sm: = tablet, lg: = desktop

## File Naming
- Pages: PascalCase in src/pages/
- Components: PascalCase in src/components/
- Data: camelCase in src/data/
- Types: PascalCase in src/types/

## Common Patterns
- Page wrapper: `<div className="min-h-screen bg-offwhite pt-20 sm:pt-24">`
- Content wrapper: `<div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">`
- Section spacing: `py-20 sm:py-28`
- Card: `bg-white rounded-2xl p-5 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1`

## DO NOT
- Never use #000000 for text
- Never use pure white (#FFFFFF) as page background
- Never add booking functionality (Phase 2 only)
- Never add dark mode
- Never change the color palette
- Never use non-Indian place references
- Never add features not in docs/CampIn_Product_Specification.md without asking
